transcript_text: There are all these studies that are saying, oh, all the people that lost weight, they  ended up getting it back in the long term.  That's really on the people when you think about it.  They didn't want to put in the work to keep the weight off.  Just like people are giving you the respect for being body positive, you shouldn't be demonizing  people that want to at least try dieting.  If your only goal is to lose weight, you might gain it back in the long term.  The thing is you need to adapt fitness and health as a lifestyle.
